    "deloadMethods": [
        {
            "name": "40/50/60 Protocol",
            "description": "The standard 5/3/1 deload week: after three hard weeks, the 4th week is a light week using approximately 40%, 50%, and 60% of your Training Max for 3 sets of 5 reps. This week is designed to facilitate recovery by doing only easy sets (no rep maxes).",
            "whenToUse": "Default deload for most 5/3/1 cycles. Wendler recommends deloading every fourth week to allow your body and mind to rest and come back stronger.",
            "exceptions": "Typically skipped in very low-frequency routines (e.g. training 1-2 times/week) where accumulated fatigue is lower. In advanced multi-cycle structures (Leader/Anchor cycles), lifters often defer the deload until after a couple of cycles, using a special 7th Week Protocol deload between Leader and Anchor phases instead.",
