            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "7th Week Protocol",
            "description": "A deload method introduced in later 5/3/1 programming (\"5/3/1 Forever\") as an alternative to the monthly deload. The 7th Week Protocol can serve as a lighter \"break\" week or a test week after several training cycles. It typically involves a week of reduced work (or a Training Max test) to recuperate or verify progress.",
            "whenToUse": "Used approximately every 6-7 weeks, often between Leader and Anchor cycles in advanced 5/3/1 templates. For example, after 2 or 3 back-to-back cycles without a deload (Leaders), a 7th Week Protocol week is inserted as the deload before proceeding to the Anchor phase.",
            "exceptions": "Not necessary if you are following the original 4-week cycle structure (which already includes a deload every 4th week). The 7th Week Protocol essentially replaces those frequent deloads with a less frequent but slightly longer break, so it's used in specific templates rather than alongside the standard deload.",
